{
  "page": "Jewelry",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Jewelry</b> is used by men and women throughout the <a href=\"/index.php/Known_world\" title=\"Known world\">known world</a> to change or enhance physical appearance.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Earrings\">Earrings</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Jewelry&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Earrings\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Earrings are rarely mentioned in text, and the word \"earring\" never appears as such. The handful of mentions made of ear piercings are actually for males with jeweled studs in their ears, or exotic foreigners not from <a href=\"/index.php/Westeros\" title=\"Westeros\">Westeros</a> (and even these are scarce).\n</p>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Ramsay_Bolton\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Ramsay Bolton\">Ramsay Bolton</a> at times wears a <a href=\"/index.php/Garnet\" title=\"Garnet\">garnet</a> in his right ear, cut into the shape of a drop of blood.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd12.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd12.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Garin_(Orphan)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Garin (Orphan)\">Garin</a>, an <a href=\"/index.php/Orphans_of_the_Greenblood\" title=\"Orphans of the Greenblood\">orphans of the Greenblood</a> from <a href=\"/index.php/Dorne\" title=\"Dorne\">Dorne</a>, wears a <a href=\"/index.php/Jade\" title=\"Jade\">jade</a> stud in one of his ears.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Lysono_Maar\" title=\"Lysono Maar\">Lysono Maar</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Spymaster\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Spymaster\">spymaster</a> for the <a href=\"/index.php/Golden_Company\" title=\"Golden Company\">Golden Company</a> in the <a href=\"/index.php/Free_Cities\" title=\"Free Cities\">Free Cities</a>, wears and inordinate amount of jewelry and cosmetics, giving him a somewhat feminine appearance. He has heavily pierced ears filled with <a href=\"/index.php/Pearl\" title=\"Pearl\">pearls</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Amethyst\" title=\"Amethyst\">amethysts</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>\n<p>It appears to be generally uncommon for men to have ear piercings in Westeros.\n</p><p>Nonetheless a stray mention is made at <a href=\"/index.php/Sansa_Stark\" title=\"Sansa Stark\">Sansa Stark</a>'s wedding to <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a> that \"<a href=\"/index.php/Moonstone\" title=\"Moonstone\">moonstones</a> hung from her ears and about her neck\" - implying that it is actually commonplace for female <a href=\"/index.php/Nobility\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Nobility\">nobility</a> in Westeros to wear earrings.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos28.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos28.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Jewelry&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Radwd12.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd12.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons-Chapter_12\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons-Chapter 12\">Chapter 12</a>, Reek I.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Raffc21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows\" title=\"A Feast for Crows\">A Feast for Crows</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows-Chapter_21\" title=\"A Feast for Crows-Chapter 21\">Chapter 21</a>, The Queenmaker.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Radwd24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons-Chapter_24\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons-Chapter 24\">Chapter 24</a>, The Lost Lord.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rasos28.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasos28.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords\" title=\"A Storm of Swords\">A Storm of Swords</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords-Chapter_28\" title=\"A Storm of Swords-Chapter 28\">Chapter 28</a>, Sansa III.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260404075344\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.025 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.027 sec